Kount Access Prerequisites
==============================================

Required information
==========================

In order to start using the Kount Access services, developers must have several configuration parameters.


+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| Resource                   | Origin / URL                                                                                                 | Type of Request   |
+============================+==============================================================================================================+===================+
| Merchant ID                | *Provided by Kount*                                                                                          |                   |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| Agent Web Console          | *Provided by Kount*                                                                                          |                   |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| API Key                    | Merchant-generated `instructions <Kount-Access-EnvironmentsAPIKeysThresholds.html#creating-an-api-key>`_     |                   |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| Device Collector Service   | *Provided by Kount*, example:``https://<kount-access-host>``                                                 |``GET``            |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| API Device ID Request      | *Provided by Kount*, ``https://<kount-access-host>/device``                                                  |``GET``            |
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| API Login Velocity Request | *Provided by Kount*, ``https://<kount-access-host>/velocity``                                                |``POST / RESPONSE``|
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| API Decision Request       | *Provided by Kount*, ``https://<kount-access-host>/decision``                                                |``POST / RESPONSE``|
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+
| API Thresholds Endpoint    | *Provided by Kount*                                                                                          |``POST / RESPONSE``|
+----------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------+

Using the *Merchant ID* and the *API Key* is mandatory for every request type available for Kount Access tools - Data Collector and Access Service.

Downloading or Install the SDK
====================================================

If you want to use the Kount Access SDK, you need to download and build it locally. There are some options for downloading:

* **Clone** the ``kount-access-python-sdk`` repository and use its `master` branch if you want to have the latest (unreleased) features, improvements and bugfixes.

* **Download** (the latest) release from the `Releases <https://github.com/Kount/kount-access-python-sdk/releases>`_ page for a stable version of the SDK.

* **pip** 
  
  ::
  
    pip install kount-access-sdk



:information_source: **This package works with Python 2.7.13 and 3.5, 3.6x**

